Veterans' Day, 1996<br>
Like a lot of others today, it's been on my mind, too.<br>
Memories, vivid and real, though twenty-five years gone.<br>
The memories haunt me. And scare me. A special kind of hell.<br>
Can I really take another twenty-five years of memories?<br>
As I sat down to type this those were my thoughts.<br>
Then my son walked up, gave me a hug, said &quot;I love you,Dad&quot;.<br>
It was then I remembered why I remember.<br>
 
